<emphasis id="A5FEEAEE7D41FFC4FEAE9F40FE3FCE6C" box="[367,477,1550,1571]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2080">A. rakitovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) 
<taxonomicName id="508A4D7F7D41FFC4FE0D9F67FDB8CE71" authorityName="Ceotto &amp; Mejdalani &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2004" box="[460,602,1577,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrobelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="2080" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nessimiani">
<emphasis id="A5FEEAEE7D41FFC4FE0D9F67FDB8CE71" box="[460,602,1577,1598]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2080">A. nessimiani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="973536FC7D42FFC7FF0699A0FBD9C9A6" blockId="10.[159,1116,173,748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="0FB12A797D42FFC7FE4A99A0FDFCC949" box="[395,542,238,262]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figures 12–16</figureCitation>
) similar to 
<taxonomicName id="508A4D7F7D42FFC7FD5999A0FCEEC949" authority="Ceotto &amp; Mejdalani &amp; Takiya, 2004" authorityName="Ceotto &amp; Mejdalani &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2004" box="[664,780,238,262]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrobelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rakitovi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="A5FEEAEE7D42FFC7FD5999A0FCEEC949" box="[664,780,238,262]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">A. rakitovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BECD57957D42FFC7FCD099A0FC8AC949" box="[785,872,238,262]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Sternite VII narrower than in the latter species and with median posterior lobe more strongly produced (
<figureCitation id="0FB12A797D42FFC7FF679860FEE9C909" box="[166,267,302,326]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 12</figureCitation>
). Pygofer apex narrowed and subacute (
<figureCitation id="0FB12A797D42FFC7FD189860FCDEC909" box="[729,828,302,326]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 13</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor with second valvulae, in lateral view, distinctly broadened beyond basal curvature, narrowing gradually toward acute apex (
<figureCitation id="0FB12A797D42FFC7FE279821FDABC9C8" box="[486,585,367,391]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 14</figureCitation>
); preapical prominence distinct (
<figureCitation id="0FB12A797D42FFC7FC6E9821FBF0C9C8" box="[943,1042,367,391]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 15</figureCitation>
); teeth triangular, distributed from beginning of expanded portion to apex, those from expanded portion larger (
<figureCitation id="0FB12A797D42FFC7FE7F98FEFDB6C987" box="[446,596,432,456]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figures 14–16</figureCitation>
); denticles from preapical prominence to apex on ventral margin and on posterior portion of median surface of teeth (
<figureCitation id="0FB12A797D42FFC7FC0A989FFBCCC9A6" box="[971,1070,465,489]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[154,170,1523,1545]" captionTargetBox="[156,1112,170,1477]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[154,1112,170,1485]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS 10–16. Female genital structures of Acrobelus rakitovi sp. nov. and A. nessimiani sp. nov. (10, 11) A. rakitovi: (10) sternite VII, ventral view; (11) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. (12–16) A. nessimiani: (12) sternite VII, ventral view; (13) pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; (14) second valvula of ovipositor, general lateral view; (15) apical portion of second valvula showing preapical prominence, ventral denticles, teeth, ducts and apical portion of ramus, lateral view; (16) median portion of second valvula showing teeth and ducts, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676113" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4676113/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">figure 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="973536FC7D42FFC7FF0698BFFBC8CA46" blockId="10.[159,1116,173,748]" box="[199,1066,497,521]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">Colour mostly reddish brown; membrane of forewings translucent brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="973536FC7D42FFC7FF069B5FFD91CAC5" blockId="10.[159,1116,173,748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">
<emphasis id="A5FEEAEE7D42FFC7FF069B5FFEAACA66" box="[199,328,529,553]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named in honour of Prof. Dr Jorge Luiz Nessimian (Departamento de Zoologia, Universidade Federal do 
<collectingRegion id="554EF81E7D42FFC7FC679B7FFBB5CA06" box="[934,1111,561,585]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="554EF81E7D42FFC7FF5E9B1CFEBBCA25" box="[159,345,594,618]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="10" pageNumber="2081">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
), whose dedication to entomology has inspired and stimulated the authors in the study of leafhoppers.
</paragraph>
